reviews.review_text: - 94 shows could be very impressive, and they could also really suck. This one is quite impressive and not very fraught with mistakes, but a little too disjointed to be one of the best of the year. Moments of greatness do abound, especially one of the craziest Uncle John's Bands ever, and what sounds like a reunion of two estranged wolf packs in the Drums/Space.

Nice show 1994 had some moments, especially earlier in the year.  Jerry was dabbling with smack, but very much the happy groom.  This show is one where his energy and tone were reminiscent of earlier years rather than the tinny sound that dominated from summer 1994 through the end of the long strange strip.  Even a Cosmic Charlie tease from a playful Jerry....   Was never a huge fan of Samson, but every now and again he nailed it [check out Charlotte, 5/3/79].  This was such a night.  Anyhow.... just felt like tossing in my 2 cents on a show that happened to pop up when I randomly chose a month and date, then looked for a show.
